# Next.js Best Practices

## Server vs Client Components
- Default to Server Components. Add `'use client'` only for useState/useEffect/browser APIs
- Place `'use client'` at leaf level (smallest boundary possible)
- Never import Server Components into Client Components — pass as `children`

## Data Fetching
- Fetch in Server Components, not useEffect
- Use `Promise.all()` for parallel independent fetches
- Server Actions = mutations only, never data fetching
- Next.js 15+: await params, cookies(), headers()

## SEO — Every Page
- `metadataBase` in root layout (required for relative OG URLs)
- `viewport` as separate export — NOT inside metadata object
- `generateMetadata()` for dynamic routes
- Canonical URL on every indexable page
- JSON-LD structured data on key pages (Organization, Product, Article, FAQ)
- Never block `/_next/` in robots.txt

## Images (next/image only)
- `priority` on the LCP image (hero/above-fold)
- Explicit `width`/`height` OR `fill` + sized container — prevents CLS
- `sizes` attribute matching actual rendered width
- `quality={85}` for hero images

## Fonts (next/font only)
- Never Google Fonts `<link>` tags or CSS `@import`
- Always `display: 'swap'`

## Scripts
- `next/script` with `strategy="afterInteractive"` for analytics
- Use `@next/third-parties/google` for GA4

## Bundle
- Direct imports — never barrel/index file imports in Client Components
- `dynamic(() => import('./Heavy'))` for non-critical heavy components

## Caching (Next.js 16)
- `'use cache'` = first statement, function must be async
- Always pair: cacheTag() + cacheLife()
- No cookies()/headers() inside 'use cache'
- updateTag() in Server Actions after mutations
- Wrap dynamic content in <Suspense>

## Core Web Vitals
- LCP < 2.5s: priority on hero image, fast TTFB, next/font
- INP < 200ms: useTransition, useDeferredValue, no blocking event handlers
- CLS < 0.1: image dimensions, font swap, min-height for async content
